:>How can you identify yourself securely over the phone, using only
:>speech?  Cryptographic signatures wouldn't apply, since I'm assuming
:
:Actually, I think one good answer would be Calling Line ID services provided
:by the phone company (have they actually got round to allowing this?  I've
:not been paying much attention I'm afraid).  The card company simply checks
:the calling phone number against a customer supplied list of valid numbers.
:It would mean the customer wouldn't be able to order from a payphone, but I
:can't see that that would be much disadvantage.

   Don't like it a bit.  Through a hole in my wall I have access to every
pair in the building, and could easily get on each pair and run up
thousands of dollars of charges to each person in the building; I assume
everyone else could do the same.
   Besides, it's not at all universal, as I was disappointed to find when
I ordered the service and found about 60% of calls are "Out of area"...
